WOW! This is really, really amazing. I have made this many times, and have had nothing but rave reviews. However, in the interest of full disclosure, I tend to be a "more is MORE" gal, so I did add a bit more of the herbs, worcester sauce, garlic, etc. to the meat. I have also just made it with leftover hamburger (without the other meats), and it was equally as good. My boyfriend ate most of the TWO loaves I made even though he was already "stuffed" (it was that good), so I froze the leftovers. Well...the next night he was begging for -- you guessed it! I didn't like serving beef two nights in a row...and tried to steer him to his other favorite: shrimp scampi. No go! The point is...is that I just nuked the frozen meatloaf in the microwave for a few minutes, and it was just as good as if I had just made it and taken it out of the oven. This recipe doesn't call for a topping, but sometimes I brush the top with a baste of ketchup, worcestershire sauce, and honey (or agave nectar). I think this would also make a great appetizer for a party as mini meatballs with the dipping sauce.

