This was really pretty easy. Watch the ground beef amount: it's 1.5 lbs, not 1 lb. I failed to notice until halfway through, at which point I had to defrost some more. Doh! Anyway...I used quick-cooking oats instead of bread crumbs for added fiber, pre-cooked (preservative-free) bacon and only 2 pcs, then sauteed the onions, etc., in the bacon drippings plus a little olive oil. Otherwise, followed the recipe exactly. There wasn't too much grease in the pan. It was a gorgeous hunk o' meat. Of course, I thought the photo w/ the recipe looked appetizing, so I may have different visual standards than most reviewers! I happily dipped mine in ketchup. My family didn't have time to do that before they had scarfed it all up. Both kids want more in their lunch tomorrow. Time & $ well- spent. P.S. I love it when people make substitutions and tell the tale in their reviews. I also love to hear from more persnickety types who follow the recipe to the letter and report on that. I've learned so much about cooking from both kinds of reviews. I only ever saw one review I thought so outrageously departed from the recipe as to be worthless. The parodies of this particular review were hilarious, though.

