As stated by numerous other reviewers, I made this with a few substitutions. Isn't that the point of meatloaf? It's basically the meat....and then ingredients to combine and make the texture and flavor appropriate. I grew up with meatloaf consisting of a Lipton Onion Soup package and an egg. Needless to say, I knew it was time to put a few cooking skills to the test. I skipped out on the prunes and bacon. I added 1 lb each of ground sirloin, pork and veal. Added a little extra garlic for zing and added an extra stalk of celery - just because I LOVE cooked celery! This recipe takes meatloaf to a gourmet level! There are so many restaurants in Manhattan that have "Mom's Meatloaf" on the menu. To me, that just means they added the soup package. THIS is what I want my son to remember for the next 50 or so years as "Mom's Meatloaf"! Good luck to all - it's delicious!

