This is my new favorite meatloaf recipe!. My favorite part of meatloaf used to be the tomato sauce topping, but no longer. My husband was a little doubtful when he saw me chopping the prunes and bacon in the food processor, but he agreed that the results were amazing. The only ground pork I could by was lean and in a 2 lb. package, so I used 2 lbs. lean pork and 2 pounds ground beef and it turned out great. I might use a little less salt next time as the bacon added some saltiness. Maybe reduce it to 1.5 tsp.

Rating: 4
I was filled with positive anticipation while preparing this recipe, partially based on the somewhat intriguing ingredients, and partially based on the predominantly positive reviews. However, I did make it low(er) fat by frying the chopped bacon until crispy before adding it to the mix, using extra-lean ground beef and lean ground pork. Also,I used rye bread to make the bread crumbs, and, as some other reviewers noted, finely chopped the celery, carrots, onion, and garlic in the food processor. The resulting meat loaf was, thankfully, not swimming in fat as in the unappetizing photograph which accompanies the recipe. In fact, I removed very little extraneous fat from the baking pan using a turkey baster about 15 minutes before the meat loaf was done. My family and I have always heartily enjoyed my "usual" meat loaf, but we were quite pleasantly surprised with how absolutely delicious this recipe turned out. It has usurped my "usual" meat loaf recipe, for sure; I would give it 5 forks if I could.

