Rating: 3
For the cook from Atlanta and Haddonfield..I learned a trick recently from Paula Deen. When preparing meatloaf don't use a loaf pan, use a 13 x 9 pan; but first place two or three slices of thick sliced, hearty white bread in the pan. The larger loaf pan allows for a larger portion of the loaf to brown, and the bread will pull away and retain that unwanted fatty liquid from the loaf. If you liked this meatloaf recipe you might want to try Paula Deen's Bacon Cheeseburger Meatloaf recipe.

