Liked it, but didn't love it. I found the chopped up bacon in the loaf to be too much.. It certainly contributed to the flavor, but somewhat dominated it. I very much liked the addition of prunes. I also like the concept of a cooked mirepoix added to the mixture. I did find the loaf to be extremely moist and somewhat crumbly... meaning, I had trouble slicing it and getting my pieces to hold together. I also needed to cook the meatloaf on 375 for 30 minutes longer than suggested in order to get the internal temperature to hit over 155 degrees. POSSIBLE MODIFICATIONS: If I make again, I will probably eliminate the bacon altogether and use a slightly leaner cut of beef to complement the ground pork. Reducing the fat and the bacon should cut down on the moisture a bit and eliminate the bacony flavor. OTHER RECOMMENDATIONS: I made a sun-dried tomato ketchup (Recipe on Epicurious.com) and spread some over the top in the last 20 minutes of cooking. It complemented the meatloaf well and was consisten with the 'high-low' concept of this dish.

